The new 
year started on a sombre note in the Western Cape where a collision 
between truck and two taxis shortly after midnight left eight people 
dead.  The accident occurred on the N1 approximately 10km outside Leeu-Gamka at 00:05 on Friday. Leeu-Gamka is a small town located 355km northeast of Cape Town in the Karoo. Western
 Cape traffic spokesperson Jandre Bakker said according to preliminary 
reports, the truck was travelling in the direction of Cape Town while 
the two taxis were travelling towards the Eastern Cape.    The driver of the truck was seriously injured.  "We ask road users to be patient." News24  